acceptOwnership().details: The new owner accepts the ownership transfer.

checkLimits(bool,uint256,address).details: Checks if the given deployment amount adheres to the defined limits.

params._asset: The address of the asset being deployed.
params._isSell: Whether the deployment is a sell.

returns._status: status code indicating the result of the check:         0:  All checks passed.         1:  Deployment per trade limit exceeded.         2:  Weekly deployment size limit exceeded.         3:  Newly purchased assets cannot sell in cooldown period.

depositAsset(uint256,uint256).details: Handles deposits after assets have been traded

params._amount: the amount of asset to deposit
params._orderId: the id of the order in AgentGeneratedIntentList

returns._0: Total count of processed order IDs

getProcessedOrderIdsRange(uint256,uint25.details: Simple range-based retrieval to avoid gas limits with large arrays

returns._0: Subset of processed order IDs within the specified range

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

params._recipient: The address to receive the tokens
params._token: The address of the token to withdraw

pendingOwner().details: Returns the address of the pending owner.

proxiableUUID().details: Implementation of the ERC-1822 {proxiableUUID} function. This returns the storage slot used by the implementation. It is used to validate the implementation's compatibility when performing an upgrade. IMPORTANT: A proxy pointing at a proxiable contract should not be considered proxiable itself, because this risks bricking a proxy that upgrades to it, by delegating to itself until out of gas. Thus it is critical that this function revert if invoked through a proxy. This is guaranteed by the `notDelegated` modifier.

publishAGI(uint8,address,uint256,address.details: Adds a new order to the `AgentGeneratedIntentList`. Only callable by the AI, owner, or Master42.      Emits an `AGIPublished` event with the order id.

params._amountToSell: Amount of the asset to sell (inputAmount)
params._assetToBuy: Address of the asset to buy, could be $SVF42 or whitelisted asset
params._assetToSell: Address of the asset to sell, could be $SVF42 or whitelisted asset
params._orderType: Type of the order (0 for regular trades)

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

setAGISolverAddress(address).details: Configuration function to update the solver address. Only callable by the owner.

params._newSolverAddress: The new solver address to set

setMaster42Address(address).details: Configuration function to update the Master42 address. Only callable by the owner.

params._newMaster42Address: The new Master42 address to set

transferOwnership(address).details: Starts the ownership transfer of the contract to a new account. Replaces the pending transfer if there is one. Can only be called by the current owner. Setting `newOwner` to the zero address is allowed; this can be used to cancel an initiated ownership transfer.

upgradeToAndCall(address,bytes).details: Upgrade the implementation of the proxy to `newImplementation`, and subsequently execute the function call encoded in `data`. Calls {_authorizeUpgrade}. Emits an {Upgraded} event.

viewAGI(uint256).details: Returns the `AgentGeneratedIntent` struct for the specified order id.      Used by the solver to sync and check the status of the order.

params._orderId: The id of the `AgentGeneratedIntent` in the `AgentGeneratedIntentList`

returns._0: The `AgentGeneratedIntent` struct corresponding to the order id
